*** ChanServ Help - Command: SET BANTYPE ***
This option lets you choose the type of ban applied to
users who join your channel and are automatically kickbanned
by ChanServ due to the Restrict option being enabled.
There are 10 ban types available, and they are:
 
  0: Ban in the *!user@host format
  1: Ban in the *!*user@host format
  2: Ban in the *!*@host format
  3: Ban in the *!*user@*.host format
  4: Ban in the *!*@*.host format
  5: Ban in the nick!user@host format
  6: Ban in the nick!*user@host format
  7: Ban in the nick!*@host format
  8: Ban in the nick!*user@*.host format
  9: Ban in the nick!*@*.host format
 
The default bantype value for a channel is 2.
 
Syntax:
/cs SET #canale BANTYPE <value>
 
Examples:
/cs SET #IRCHelp BANTYPE 4
/cs SET #debian BANTYPE 7
 
Type /join #IRCHelp for more information.
*** End of Help ***